Program: Discovery
Title: The Priomordial Slime
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx5z
Last Broadcast Date: 14 August 1998
A look back to 400 million years ago when algae learnt to reproduce out of water. Scientists are looking at the evolution of land plants from slime. Also in the programme, the reason folic acid is so successful in preventing spina bifida in newborns and putative proof of global warming, or is it?